---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import { GITHUB_ISSUES_URL, GITHUB_REPO_URL } from "../lib/site";
---

<Base
  title="Privacy policy · Cloud Speech"
  description="Privacy policy for Cloud Speech: your credentials stay in your browser, selected text goes only to the provider you choose, no analytics or tracking."
  active="privacy"
>
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-12">
    <p><a class="link text-sm text-body" href="../">← Home</a></p>

    <header class="mt-8">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">Privacy policy</h1>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted">Last updated: July 2026</p>
      <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-body">
        This policy covers the Cloud Speech extension and its sibling listings (Polly
        for Chrome and Azure Speech for Chrome). The short version: the extension has no servers,
        no analytics, and no tracking. Your text goes only to the cloud provider you choose, using
        your own credentials.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Introduction</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-body">
        This Privacy Policy explains how Cloud Speech ("we," "our," or "us") handles your
        information. The extension is
        open source. You can verify everything below in the
        <a class="link" href={GITHUB_REPO_URL}>source code</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Information the extension stores</h2>

      <h3 class="mt-5 font-semibold">API credentials</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-body">
        The extension stores the API credentials you provide for Amazon Polly (access key, secret
        key, region), Azure Speech (key, region), Google Cloud Text-to-Speech (API key), and/or
        OpenAI (API key) in your browser using the browser's extension storage API
        (<span class="value">browser.storage</span>). They are used solely to authenticate with the
        provider you selected and are never transmitted to us or to any other third party. We
        operate no servers.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-body">
        By default, settings use Chrome's sync storage, so they follow you across devices signed
        into the same Chrome profile (Google encrypts synced extension data in transit and at
        rest). The extension has a <strong>sync toggle</strong>: turn it off in Settings to keep
        credentials in local storage on the current device only.
      </p>

      <h3 class="mt-5 font-semibold">User preferences</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-body">
        Your voice selection, favorites, playback settings, and extension configuration are stored
        the same way (sync or local, per the toggle above).
      </p>

      <h3 class="mt-5 font-semibold">Selected text</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-body">
        When you select text for speech synthesis, it is processed locally in your browser
        (sanitized and split into chunks) and sent <strong>directly and only</strong> to the one
        provider you have selected (Amazon Polly, Azure Speech, Google Cloud, or OpenAI) over
        HTTPS using your own credentials. We do not store, log, or have any access to this
        content.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">What the extension does NOT do</h2>
      <ul
        class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-1.5 pl-5 text-sm leading-relaxed text-body marker:text-faint"
      >
        <li>No analytics, telemetry, or usage tracking of any kind</li>
        <li>No advertising and no third-party trackers</li>
        <li>No selling, trading, or transferring of your data; we never see it</li>
        <li>
          No servers of our own: the only network traffic is between your browser and the speech
          provider you configured
        </li>
        <li>No sending of your text to providers you have not selected</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Third-party services</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-body">
        When you use the extension, selected text is sent from your browser to the provider you
        chose, under your own account. How that provider handles the data is governed by its own
        privacy policy:
      </p>
      <ul
        class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-1.5 pl-5 text-sm leading-relaxed text-body marker:text-faint"
      >
        <li>
          <a class="link" href="https://aws.amazon.com/privacy/">Amazon (AWS) Privacy Notice</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a class="link" href="https://privacy.microsoft.com/privacystatement"
            >Microsoft Privacy Statement</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a class="link" href="https://cloud.google.com/terms/cloud-privacy-notice"
            >Google Cloud Privacy Notice</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a class="link" href="https://openai.com/policies/privacy-policy/"
            >OpenAI Privacy Policy</a
          >
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Data storage and security</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-body">
        All extension data lives in your browser's extension storage, inside your browser
        profile. Your credentials and preferences never leave your browser except for direct,
        HTTPS-encrypted communication with the provider you configured (and, if sync is
        enabled, your browser's own settings sync).
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Your rights and control</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-body">
        Because everything is stored in your browser, you have complete control:
      </p>
      <ul
        class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-1.5 pl-5 text-sm leading-relaxed text-body marker:text-faint"
      >
        <li>Update or remove your credentials at any time in the extension's Settings</li>
        <li>Turn off settings sync to keep everything on the current device only</li>
        <li>Delete all stored data by removing the extension</li>
        <li>
          Revoke the extension's access entirely by deleting or rotating the API keys in your
          provider's console
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-body">
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes are posted on this page with
        an updated "Last updated" date, and the page history is available in the
        <a class="link" href={GITHUB_REPO_URL}
          >GitHub repository</a
        >.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Contact</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-body">
        Questions about this policy? Open an issue on
        <a class="link" href={GITHUB_ISSUES_URL}>GitHub</a
        >.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>
